      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Warn on stored data model changes",
        "body": "Closes https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/225\n\nSummary:\n- add a stored-data-model detector alongside the existing config-surface detector\n- persist `data_model_change` and `data_model_surfaces` in durable review report frontmatter\n- render a public warning naming likely persistent surfaces without calling the PR buggy by default\n- block repair/automerge pass markers for material stored-data-model changes unless the report contains adequate migration or upgrade compatibility proof\n- update review prompt guidance for stored schema, migration, vector/embedding metadata, serialized JSON state, cache schema, Durable Object, hosted storage, doctor, repair, and backfill changes\n\nImplementation notes:\n- keep detection scoped to `openclaw/openclaw` PR files and compact pull-file patches\n- fail closed on truncated pull files or missing/truncated patches for likely data-model surfaces\n- treat SQL DDL/migrations, database schema installers/helpers, persistent cache schemas, Durable Object/storage schema code, serialized JSON state written to disk/database, vector or embedding row identity/query-compatibility metadata, and doctor/migration/repair backfills as candidate surfaces\n- avoid positives for pure query-only changes and non-semantic docs wording\n\nValidation:\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\nRelease note context:\n- ClawSweeper now surfaces persistent data-model compatibility risk before automerge instead of silently passing material schema changes without migration or upgrade evidence.\n\nClawSweeper 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: issue-openclaw-clawsweeper-225\n- Source PRs: none\n- Credit: Source issue: https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/225 by @osolmaz.; Related implementation pattern: https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/171.; Do not edit CHANGELOG.md; preserve release-note context in the PR body.\n- Validation: pnpm check:changed\n- Replacement reason: ClawSweeper could not update the source PR branch directly, so it opened a writable replacement PR instead.\n\nfish notes: reasoning high; reviewed against 4784fc0e413a.\n",
